cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification using deep learning models, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel multi-scale deep learning model, which involves training deep neural networks, making it likely to also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves experiments and evaluations of the proposed model, which could also place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves learning discriminative features, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves surveillance videos, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
